HEADWORD: Iceman
<hw>Ice"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Icemen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A man who is
skilled in traveling upon ice, as among glaciers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who deals in ice; one who retails or delivers
ice.</def></p>

<p><-- The Iceman Cometh (Title of a book) -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ice plant</ent>⟦br⟧
